<subSubSection id="A8A1C85DD51F80FC14A3B3D191DA4A94" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="175540F438CFBF911E0604ED7D4AA199" pageNumber="2">
Diagnosis. Distinguished from the two other known South American freshwater sciaenid genera (
<taxonomicName id="0396EEEA15176D560581ACC68035C4A9" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:F85FE3B0-DEB1-4A78-B6EB-E88E243F54A6" class="Diplopoda" family="Platyrhacidae" genus="Pachyurus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pachyurus Agassiz 1831:125, 127" order="Polydesmida" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Pachyurus</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="466C26E0F2D3A6D56F0A0078E60990A9" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:B27B431C-FC51-4ABC-B9FC-28F9655026C6" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sciaenidae" genus="Plagioscion" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Plagioscion Gill 1861:82" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Plagioscion</taxonomicName>
) by the following combination of characters: mouth inferior, presence of three mental barbels, the swimbladder with a pair log posterior branches projecting from shorter paired anterior appendages (Fig. 1), and presence of the expanded haemal spine on the first caudal vertebra (Fig. 2). Gender masculine.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="7F7E8D5A291215F74C8758A609F1A4DD" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="75142BEC51CEEAB2D61B81065E72C194" pageNumber="2">
Comments. According to Sasaki (1989), 
<taxonomicName id="A3D96C5897B1A4F158B5585CDCA26A88" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:A1A52A20-86AC-4DC1-89BB-A5D1CC1CBBDB" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sciaenidae" genus="Pachypops" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pachypops Gill 1861:87" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Pachypops</taxonomicName>
is characterized phylogenetically by its swimbladder with a pair of anterior appendages (see Fig. 1), the possession of an unpored median barbel, and the possession of a pair of mental barbels. An unpublished phylogenetic study of South American freshwater sciaenids done by the author of the present paper reveals that the species of 
<taxonomicName id="9B865EA949FA64AF17FDA5E5E7EE21F3" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:A1A52A20-86AC-4DC1-89BB-A5D1CC1CBBDB" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sciaenidae" genus="Pachypops" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pachypops Gill 1861:87" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Pachypops</taxonomicName>
share not only those synapomorphies listed by Sasaki (1989) but also an expanded haemal spine on the first caudal vertebra (see Fig. 2). These four synapomorphies are assumed to be homoplastic with other perciforms in the final most parsimonious phylogeny.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="0551EF376366B544C094693FF374D158" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="7137F1A7F13F08E927A729C075F834FE" pageNumber="4">
Jordan and Eigenmann (1889: 413) assigned 
<taxonomicName id="471925DB876E596A54D40A3CF9625F20" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:D0D45D89-82A0-44EE-875D-56D6DD37C678" class="Diplopoda" family="Platyrhacidae" genus="Pachyurus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pachyurus Lepipterus adspersus Steindachner 1879:123 [5]" order="Polydesmida" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="adspersus">Pachyurus adspersus Steindachner 1879</taxonomicName>
to the genus 
<taxonomicName id="78AB9BD82EAEA3181365A64B52DBA7D5" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:A1A52A20-86AC-4DC1-89BB-A5D1CC1CBBDB" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sciaenidae" genus="Pachypops" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pachypops Gill 1861:87" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="4" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Pachypops</taxonomicName>
. However, despite bearing three mental barbels and six mental pores, 
<taxonomicName id="D13F1BA279CB2EDF87E1FDF950759EA3" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:D0D45D89-82A0-44EE-875D-56D6DD37C678" class="Diplopoda" family="Platyrhacidae" genus="Pachyurus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pachyurus Lepipterus adspersus Steindachner 1879:123 [5]" order="Polydesmida" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="adspersus">P. adspersus</taxonomicName>
lacks the expanded haemal spine and the appendages on the swimbladder, which occur in 
<taxonomicName id="00557603AEF8E09E86EBF4EF696CD2CD" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:A1A52A20-86AC-4DC1-89BB-A5D1CC1CBBDB" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sciaenidae" genus="Pachypops" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pachypops Gill 1861:87" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="4" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Pachypops</taxonomicName>
. Casatti (2001) considered 
<taxonomicName id="BC0FE353323CFEACAA7F2A0A3DFA8756" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:D0D45D89-82A0-44EE-875D-56D6DD37C678" class="Diplopoda" family="Platyrhacidae" genus="Pachyurus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pachyurus Lepipterus adspersus Steindachner 1879:123 [5]" order="Polydesmida" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="adspersus">P. adspersus</taxonomicName>
a member of 
<taxonomicName id="986DD5279DEB278F62742C70F3C0A7B4" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:F85FE3B0-DEB1-4A78-B6EB-E88E243F54A6" class="Diplopoda" family="Platyrhacidae" genus="Pachyurus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pachyurus Agassiz 1831:125, 127" order="Polydesmida" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Pachyurus</taxonomicName>
as originally proposed by Steindachner. An expanded haemal spine on the first caudal vertebra is also present in some other examined perciforms (the haemulid 
<taxonomicName id="7066E002363B6AF17D655311BBBE9235" class="Actinopterygii" family="Haemulidae" genus="Haemulon" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="4" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="steindachneri">Haemulon steindachneri</taxonomicName>
, the polynemid 
<taxonomicName id="7DCDA1EAA4EABABAE6DABB9C0EE88D21" class="Actinopterygii" family="Polynemidae" genus="Polydactylus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="4" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="virginicus">Polydactylus virginicus</taxonomicName>
, and the sciaenids 
<taxonomicName id="7D10CAFF29F5296F97D535EF6E46FB84" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sciaenidae" genus="Dendrophysa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="4" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="russelli">Dendrophysa russelli</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="79C8ACFEAE68AAB6F6AE20F0B3ADA6B9" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sciaenidae" genus="Kathala" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="4" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="axillaris">Kathala axillaris</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="211FF6BB66414B14233A7DE8400BB19E" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sciaenidae" genus="Plagioscion" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="4" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="auratus">Plagioscion auratus</taxonomicName>
, pers. obser.) but it is interpreted as having been independently derived in these taxa.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B707808FEE6313E6EC56BF4594470A7F" pageNumber="4">
Based on the barbel morphology 
<taxonomicName id="0B474EB713A1107F6BBB17D521B470BC" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:B0D8702C-99BE-4E65-926C-A901941132BB" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sciaenidae" genus="Pachypops" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pachypops cevegei Cervigón 1982:237" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="4" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="cevegei">
Pachypops cevegei 
<normalizedToken id="0B602EADAFDB298A85264F785F196317" originalValue="Cervigón">Cervigon</normalizedToken>
1982
</taxonomicName>
is not a species of 
<taxonomicName id="CE3A946C4A33CB92C5DC62446F4F8BC1" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:A1A52A20-86AC-4DC1-89BB-A5D1CC1CBBDB" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sciaenidae" genus="Pachypops" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pachypops Gill 1861:87" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="4" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Pachypops</taxonomicName>
, but instead a species of 
<taxonomicName id="36B49CB2674F8DC661776F18E66B7F15" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:CB92F15C-B6D6-492D-8A48-2271D89872D3" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sciaenidae" genus="Micropogonias" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Micropogonias Bonaparte 1831:170" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="4" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Micropogonias</taxonomicName>
. Therefore, of six nominal species of 
<taxonomicName id="89FC5932B6B44DF44913BAAA7A8AE206" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:A1A52A20-86AC-4DC1-89BB-A5D1CC1CBBDB" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sciaenidae" genus="Pachypops" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pachypops Gill 1861:87" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="4" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Pachypops</taxonomicName>
according to previous authors, two (
<taxonomicName id="96C4CBB28A3676AC99C4CC09AD224D46" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sciaenidae" genus="Pachypops" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="4" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="adspersus">Pachypops adspersus</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4A43352E447464A2DF66E78BB9F1821D" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:B0D8702C-99BE-4E65-926C-A901941132BB" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sciaenidae" genus="Pachypops" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pachypops cevegei Cervigón 1982:237" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="4" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="cevegei">Pachypops cevegei</taxonomicName>
) are not assignable to the genus. The remaining nominal species are discussed below under “Comments” for 
<taxonomicName id="D00F9DDFAB772043E8C26D37587CC5F8" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sciaenidae" genus="Pachypops" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="4" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="fourcroi">Pachypops fourcroi</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="99CDBB3C4C53E0752A02DFA11D2479A3" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sciaenidae" genus="Pachypops" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="4" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="trifilis">Pachypops trifilis</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="EBAB98F65CE80B98EA7D983886CA4146" type="key">
